{
  "texts": [
    "The parameters of interest, β y, measure how labor market outcomes for adopters changed in year y after the introduction of AI chatbots, compared to the period before their arrival.",
    "We estimate Equation (2) by OLS and cluster the standard errors by workplace-occupation level.",
    "Panel (a) begins by presenting differences in means, controlling for workers' predetermined characteristics-occupation, gender, age, and experience.",
    "Adopters appear to earn substantial premia of about 9% for those with employer-encouraged usage and 4% for those without.",
    "However, leveraging the panel dimension of our administrative data reveals that these earnings differentials entirely predate the arrival of AI chatbots."
  ]
}